Hello there. I bought KSP few days ago, but i have a issue.When i play game (especially launch screen) game freezes and not responding ( before error mouse icon changes to loading icon ) .I played demo of KSP, and i didn't take any problem (it's some months ago, it can be linked with my OS version ) I already writed to support.But i see on other forums there is many players takes this problem.You can see whats going on this screenshot.

Installed Mods : 

Kerbal Engineer Redux 

System Info:

Macbook Air (13-inch Early 2015 )

Intel Core i5 [4 CPUs] @ 1.6 GHz

Intel HD 6000 1538Mb GPU 1440x900 Res. 

4GB Ram 

macOS Sierra version 10.12.2

===============================================================

Notes : Here's my KSP.log , i hope thats all enough for help.Thanks.

KSP.log

PLEASE READ : If you have issues with 1.2 on macOS please feedback here, we need your problems for solve my issue and yours too.

Edited January 12, 2017 by sauerkrautpie
NOTE : I closed Higlight FX, Underwater FX.The problem is going to decrease , but still continue.

Hi @sauerkrautpie, do you have this issue when using a fresh install of KSP with no mods?

The next time this happens please try leaving the game running for a few minutes to see if it responds again, and please open Files and find your Player.log in /Library/Logs>Unity

More info on logs here.

I delete mod, and cleaned KSP. When i play in screen and low res. game is god.After i take fullscreen its continue to work but it crashed again when i name to my rocket.And i cant find any file like Player.log and Unity folder in Logs folder. It is secret file? @sal_vager

NOTE: Highlighter and Underwater FXs are still closed.When i closed them the problem going to decrease.It can be graphical.And yes i always have this problem.

NOTE2: When it freezes in fullscreen and i do cmd+TAB i can't open application again when it runs.In screen mode its same but i can see last frame only, its not going to give any response

Yes it may be a hidden file, also please try disabling the anti-aliasing in KSP's settings screen.
There is no folder named Unity, but after i disabled anti-aliasing, i didn't have any crash.It can be solve of problem, but i'll wait for being sure.Thanks for help
Good luck sauerkrautpie.

Your terrain issue looks like the same issue caused by using anti-aliasing with Intel graphics hardware, with anti-aliasing off it should work.

Thanks for the Player.log @sauerkrautpie, unfortunately it just stops, the same as the KSP.log, and does not show any errors.

I will move this to unmodded support, hopefully other macOS users will be able to help.

MacOS recently updated to 10.12.2 (December 14, 2016; 26 days ago), and macOS has been known to break the Unity3D game engine on which KSP was made.

I would like to hear from other players on macOS 10.12.2 as this may be a wider issue.
